      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(DimensionMap d)
        Return a comparaison with another DimensionMap. This DimensionMap can be overdefined compared to d and still return 0. Thus, A = B doesn't necessarily mean B = A but having this behavior allows us to access items in maps sorted by DimensionMaps with overdefined DimensionMaps. In other words, if we have an array of rois on a single image, we can use the DimensionMap of the rois to access the appropriate image in the imageSet by simply using the get method for a TreeMap with DimensionMap key and String value.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<DimensionMap>
